*   **`if (!p->activated)`**: This line accesses the `activated` member of the structure pointed to by `p`. It checks if the `activated` flag is false (i.e., the pcap handle is not activated).
*   **`return (p->version_major);`**: This line accesses the `version_major` member of the structure pointed to by `p`. It retrieves the major version number stored in this field.

